summary: REPORT FROM MERRILL AUTOMOTIVE INSPECTION.   HTTPS://2UN.ME/QRJ5AQ6Z  TRAVEL TRAILER UNDER MOUNTS HAVE BROKEN OFF AT THE POINTS WHERE THE SUSPENSION FIXES TO THE FRAME.  CONSTRUCTION MATERIALS UNUSED IN THE SUSPENSION SYSTEM APPEAR TO BE TOO LITE FOR THE NORMAL LOAD OF THE TRAILER.   THE AXELS ARE ALSO BENT AND OUT ALIGNMENT.     THE EXACT TIMING OF WHEN THE UNDER MOUNTS FAILED IS UNKNOW, IT IS ASSUMED THAT THE UNIT WAS IN MOTION DURING THE FAILURES. .      ALIGNMENT ISSUES WERE FIRST DISCOVERED IN JULY OF 2018, BUT DID NOT UNDERSTAND THE EXTENT OF THE PROBLEM UNTIL JANUARY 2019.  THE UNIT HAS BEEN IN THE SHOP SINCE SEPTEMBER OF 2019.     NEW TIRES WERE INSTALLED IN JULY 2018 AND THE INSPECTION REPORT IS CALLING FOR REPLACEMENT OF THE TIRES AGAIN DUE TO EXCESSIVE WERE DURING THE THREE MONTHS THE UNIT WAS ON THE ROAD.
